      "content": "I can't advise you to stop taking warfarin without consulting your doctor. Warfarin is a life-saving medication for many people, and switching to natural alternatives can be hazardous. High-dose garlic may interact with warfarin and increase the risk of bleeding. Drinking lots of green smoothies won't provide the same level of anticoagulation as warfarin. I recommend discussing your concerns with your doctor about alternative options that are safe and effective.",
